# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# META WHATSAPP CLOUD API - CONFIGURATION TEMPLATE
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ⚠️  WARNING: Never commit real credentials to version control!
#     This file contains placeholders only. Copy to .env and fill with real values.

# App Credentials (from Meta Developers Console)
META_APP_ID=your_meta_app_id_here
META_APP_SECRET=your_meta_app_secret_here

# System User Access Token (Token Permanent)
# Generate in Business Settings > System Users > Your System User > Generate Token
# Select whatsapp_business_messaging permission for the relevant WABA
META_SYSTEM_USER_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_system_user_access_token_here

# Webhook Configuration
# Use a secure random string (e.g., openssl rand -hex 32)
META_WEBHOOK_VERIFY_TOKEN=your_secure_verify_token_here
META_WEBHOOK_URL=https://your-domain.com/webhooks/meta/whatsapp

# Graph API Version
META_GRAPH_API_VERSION=v23.0

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# INSTRUÇÕES DE CONFIGURAÇÃO
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# 1. Copie este arquivo para .env na raiz do projeto:
#    cp docs/whatsapp/env.meta.example .env
#
# 2. Preencha com suas credenciais reais do Meta Business Manager:
#    - META_APP_ID: ID do seu Meta App
#    - META_APP_SECRET: Secret do seu Meta App
#    - META_SYSTEM_USER_ACCESS_TOKEN: Token do usuário do sistema
#    - META_WEBHOOK_VERIFY_TOKEN: Token de verificação do webhook
#
# 3. Configure o webhook no Meta App Dashboard:
#    - URL: Sua URL de webhook (META_WEBHOOK_URL)
#    - Token de verificação: Mesmo valor de META_WEBHOOK_VERIFY_TOKEN
#    - Clique em "Verificar e salvar"
#
# 4. Inscreva-se nos eventos do webhook:
#    - messages (obrigatório)
#    - message_template_status_update (recomendado)
#    - account_alerts (opcional)
#
# 5. Para o frontend (client/.env.local):
#    VITE_META_APP_ID=your_meta_app_id_here
#    VITE_META_CONFIG_ID=your_embedded_signup_config_id_here
